No use looking at me
like that.

31:20.811 --> 31:22.647
It's the gullet
for you, mister.

31:25.416 --> 31:28.319
Hey. Sorry. I kind of
got caught up.

31:29.221 --> 31:30.388
No. It's okay.

31:32.959 --> 31:36.095
You know,
if rats could dance,

31:36.127 --> 31:37.997
they probably
wouldn't gnaw so much.

31:40.332 --> 31:42.934
Hey, come on.
We're just
gettin' started.

31:44.569 --> 31:46.305
I think I'm gonna
sit this one out.
MAN: Uh-uh.

31:46.337 --> 31:49.208
You can't just work us up
like that and then just--
Hey!

31:49.240 --> 31:53.845
-I think she said no.
-Well, nobody
asked you, Ellen.

31:58.616 --> 32:01.252
-You wanna dance?
-That's all.

32:01.287 --> 32:04.155
Nice, slow,
relaxing dance.

32:14.099 --> 32:17.603
Gee.
I think I do
feel more relaxed.

32:19.105 --> 32:20.939
XANDER:
Aha! I got it!

32:20.972 --> 32:22.340
Here's our villain
right here.

32:25.711 --> 32:26.979
What?

32:27.012 --> 32:29.315
That's a D&D manual,
sweetie.

32:29.347 --> 32:31.782
No, but it--

32:34.452 --> 32:36.622
-Oh.
-Let's face it.

32:36.654 --> 32:39.090
We're not gonna find this thing
because it doesn't exist.

32:39.125 --> 32:42.594
There's no such thing
as a frost monster
who eats diamonds.

32:42.627 --> 32:45.131
Well, maybe
he doesn't eat them.

32:45.163 --> 32:48.000
You know, maybe he just...
thinks they're pretty.

32:51.136 --> 32:55.040
-We suck.
-We need new brains.

32:55.074 --> 32:58.376
-What's up with Willow?
-Out with Amy, I guess.

32:58.410 --> 33:00.979
Great. Someone to do
more magic with.

33:01.012 --> 33:05.951
But at least she's not
all cooped up and crying.
That's forward momentum.

33:05.983 --> 33:09.188
I know that I don't know
everything that happened
with her and Tara, but it--

33:09.221 --> 33:13.625
Tara thinks Willow is
doing too much magic,
and she's not the only one.

33:13.659 --> 33:17.296
I know. But I think she'll
be fine, you know?

33:17.328 --> 33:20.132
It's-- It's Willow,
she of the level head.

33:20.165 --> 33:24.303
Well, those are the ones you
have to watch out for the most.
Responsible types.

33:24.336 --> 33:28.074
Right. She might
go crazy and start
alphabetizing everything.

33:28.106 --> 33:31.910
I'm serious.
Responsible people
are always so concerned

33:31.942 --> 33:35.213
with being good all the time
that when they finally
get a taste of being bad,

33:35.247 --> 33:38.849
they can't get enough--
It's like all kablooey.

33:38.884 --> 33:42.688
-That's not true.
-Okay, not kablooey.
More like bam!

33:42.721 --> 33:45.356
It's human nature, Buff.

33:45.391 --> 33:48.660
Wil's getting a taste of
something powerful,
way bigger than her.

33:48.693 --> 33:51.863
Yeah, and she was getting
out of control with it
before Tara left,

33:51.896 --> 33:56.234
-and now that she's gone--
-XANDER: It's gotta be seductive
just giving in to it,

33:56.268 --> 33:57.969
going totally wild.

33:59.570 --> 34:02.240
-We need to keep
an eye on her.
-Okay.

34:02.273 --> 34:04.509
Okay. We'll--
we'll keep an eye.

34:04.542 --> 34:07.413
But we can't assume that
everybody's getting seduced.
You know, sometimes--

34:07.445 --> 34:10.148
(phone rings)

34:14.119 --> 34:17.289
-Hello, Magic Box.
-Slayer.

34:17.322 --> 34:21.693
-Spike?
-Meet me at the cemetery.

34:21.726 --> 34:24.795
Twenty minutes.
Come alone.

34:25.896 --> 34:28.567
-Spike?
-(sighs)

34:28.599 --> 34:31.202
Bloody hell.
Yes, it's me.

34:31.237 --> 34:35.806
-You're calling me
on the phone?
-Just be there.

34:35.840 --> 34:39.143
Why, are you
helping again?

34:39.177 --> 34:41.480
You have a lead on
this frost monster thingie?

34:41.512 --> 34:43.815
Something like that, yeah.

34:43.849 --> 34:46.117
Thought you might be up
for a little grunt work.

34:46.152 --> 34:49.655
What? No.
No-No grunting.

34:51.822 --> 34:56.561
I was talking shop, love,
but if you got other
ideas, you, me,

34:56.594 --> 34:58.130
cozy little
tomb with a view--

35:04.101 --> 35:06.637
So, what did
Captain Peroxide want?

35:06.672 --> 35:10.007
Nothing. He just, you know,
wanted to see if I--

35:10.041 --> 35:13.445
I wanted to patrol for
the-the monster.

35:13.478 --> 35:16.215
But I-I told him
that I... would not.

35:19.985 --> 35:23.355
BUFFY: I'm telling you.
I think there's something
about this thing.

35:23.389 --> 35:26.492
I don't know, Buff.
It seems like we've
been through every book.

35:26.525 --> 35:29.494
Yeah, even the ones
that weren't so boring
you wanted to kill yourself.

35:29.527 --> 35:33.199
We have those?
I'm just saying, all the things
that have happened lately--

35:33.231 --> 35:36.335
Okay, the--
the bank robbery,
the jewelry heist.

35:36.367 --> 35:40.206
-Exploding lint.
-Is it me or do these
things seem really--

35:40.239 --> 35:41.206
Lame?

35:43.141 --> 35:45.210
Well, I was gonna go
with unusual, but yeah.

35:47.179 --> 35:49.146
I don't know.
I'll do a quick
patrol tonight,

35:49.181 --> 35:51.682
and after a good night's sleep,
we can solve this tomorrow.

35:51.717 --> 35:54.119
Optimism.
I remember optimism.

35:54.152 --> 35:57.789
-That's because you're
like a thousand.
-Good night, guys.

35:57.822 --> 35:58.824
Night.
Night.

36:04.695 --> 36:05.831
Slayer.

36:05.864 --> 36:08.233
And so my night
is now complete.

36:08.266 --> 36:12.438
You never showed.
Sorry. Little busy
actually doing stuff.

36:12.538 --> 36:14.572
You shouldn't
be so flip, love.

36:14.606 --> 36:16.407
What are you gonna do,
walk behind me to death?

36:16.442 --> 36:18.277
I'm just saying things
might be a little different.

36:19.945 --> 36:23.114
You ought to be careful.
Enough.

36:26.251 --> 36:29.588
Get out of my way.
Or what?

36:40.266 --> 36:44.235
(panting)
Oh, the pain, the pain...

36:44.269 --> 36:46.204
is gone.

36:47.405 --> 36:50.442
Guess what
I just found out.

36:50.476 --> 36:53.043
Looks like I'm not as toothless
as you thought, sweetheart.

36:54.413 --> 36:55.746
How?

36:55.780 --> 36:59.885
Don't you get it?
Don't you see?

36:59.918 --> 37:02.387
You came back wrong.

37:20.838 --> 37:24.074
It's a trick.
You did something to
the chip. It's a trick.

37:24.108 --> 37:26.945
It's no trick.
It's not me. It's you.

37:26.978 --> 37:30.481
Just you, in fact.
That's the funny part.
You're the one that's changed.

37:30.516 --> 37:32.918
That's why
this doesn't hurt me.

37:34.786 --> 37:36.954
Came back a little
less human than you were.

37:37.856 --> 37:39.358
You're wrong.

37:42.460 --> 37:45.963
Then how come
you're so spooked, love?
And why can I--

37:45.996 --> 37:46.998
do that?

37:52.003 --> 37:53.038
You're wrong.

